---
/**
 * ScrollText — a featured line whose color fills in as it scrolls through the
 * viewport (the "scroll-synced text" effect). Implemented with pure CSS:
 * `background-clip: text` + a scroll-driven `animation-timeline: view()` (see
 * the `.fx-scrolltext` rules in global.css).
 *
 * Progressive enhancement: browsers without scroll-driven animations — or users
 * with reduced motion / no JS — simply get solid, fully-colored text. Must be
 * placed where it can be scrolled *through* (i.e. not above the fold).
 *
 * Content comes from the default slot. Colors use --color-* tokens, so it
 * follows light/dark themes automatically.
 */
---

<p class="fx-scrolltext"><slot /></p>
